 We do not curve in this class; 89.9
is still considered a B
Rather, we teach to proficiency, setting clear expectations of what you need to accomplish to earn an A
If he is participating in class or the group project, and making adjustments based on our feedback, he should expect an A with just fulfilling the basic requirements
To ensure inclusiveness and avoid exclusion of students, he will be assigned to a project group based on results of a skill survey to ensure that technical experience is balanced across the different project groups
Any additional items added later to the rubric count as extra credit, hence there is no obligation to comply with the requirement; you can still get an A fulfilling the basic requirements
o Final code (that is clean and understandable), submitted in the assigned GitHub Classroom repository, and any other supporting documentation (e.g.
